sees-trump-victory-as-apps-best-hope%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemployees%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20rely%20on%20TikTok%20to%20make%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20things%20stand%2C%20TikTok%20is%20still%20marching%20toward%20its%20demise%20due%20to%20an%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsenate-passes-tiktok-ban-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApril%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0passed%20by%20Congress%20that%20forces%20its%20owner%2C%20ByteDance%2C%20to%20either%20divest%20from%20its%20US%20assets%20or%20face%20a%20ban%20from%20app%20stores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok%20is%20challenging%20the%20law%20in%20the%20US%20Court%20of%20Appeals%20for%20the%20District%20of%20Columbia%20Circuit.%20So%20far%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-justice-department-federal-appeals-court-law-ban-expert-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eit's%20not%20going%20great%20for%20the%20company%3C%2Fa%3E.%20TikTok%20is%20making%20a%20free-speech%20argument%20against%20alleged%20national%20security%20concerns%20tied%20to%20its%20owner%20being%20based%20in%20China%2C%20which%20the%20US%20government%20has%20designated%20a%20foreign%20adversary.%20The%20DC%20Circuit%20often%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ban-bill-is-first-amendment-disaster-may-survive-courts-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshows%20deference%20to%20Congress%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20national%20security.%20The%20case%20may%20ultimately%20end%20up%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20court%20intervention%2C%20the%20app%20is%20set%20to%20be%20either%20sold%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Ftechnology%2Fbytedance-prefers-tiktok-shutdown-us-if-legal-options-fail-sources-say-2024-04-25%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunlikely%3C%2Fa%3E)%20or%20banned%20on%20January%2019%2C%20the%20day%20before%20the%20inauguration.%20Before%20leaving%20office%2C%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20has%20the%20option%20to%20extend%20that%20deadline%20by%2090%20days%2C%20and%20he%20hasn't%20indicated%20he%20will%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegal%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20TikTok's%20future%20in%20the%20US%20is%20still%20very%20much%20in%20question%20despite%20Trump's%20election%20win.%20The%20company%20has%20to%20prevail%20in%20the%20courts%20first%20to%20give%20its%20app%20a%20shot%20at%20sticking%20around%2C%20as%20Trump%20can't%20simply%20repeal%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20the%20law%20was%20enacted%20by%20Congress%2C%20I'm%20not%20sure%20how%20much%20wiggle%20room%20a%20future%20Trump%20administration%20would%20have%20to%20ignore%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20G.S.%20Hans%2C%20a%20clinical%20professor%20of%20law%20at%20Cornell%20Law%20School%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20could%20try%20to%20persuade%20Congress%20to%20repeal%20or%20change%20the%20law%2C%20although%20that%20seems%20unlikely%2C%20said%20Matthew%20Schettenhelm%2C%20a%20litigation%20and%20policy%20analyst%20at%20Bloomberg%20Intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20TikTok%20loses%20the%20case%2C%20as%20I%20expect%2C%20it's%20much%20harder%20to%20see%20Trump%20stopping%20the%20ban%20from%20taking%20effect%20on%20January%2019%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20two%20options%20to%20try%20to%20rescue%20TikTok%20once%20in%20office.%20Neither%20of%20them%20is%20straightforward%2C%20legal%20sources%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fb3fb3bc-ea37-4e4d-85a0-a6b8468f562e%5C%22%3EStrategy%20one%3A%20Don't%20enforce%20the%20law%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20could%20guard%20TikTok%20by%20asking%20his%20Justice%20Department%20not%20to%20enforce%20the%20Protecting%20Americans%20from%20Foreign%20Adversary%20Controlled%20Applications%20Act%20regarding%20TikTok.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20some%20history%20with%20Justice%20Departments%20or%20the%20president%20taking%20issue%20with%20a%20law%20that's%20on%20the%20books%2C%20not%20enforcing%20it%2C%20potentially%20declaring%20it%20unlawful%20itself%2C%20or%20refusing%20to%20defend%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Aram%20A.%20Gavoor%2C%20a%20former%20Justice%20Department%20senior%20counsel%20who%20now%20serves%20as%20associate%20dean%20for%20academic%20affairs%20at%20the%20George%20Washington%20University%20Law%20School.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20example%2C%20Gavoor%20pointed%20to%20the%20decision%20by%20former%20president%20Barack%20Obama's%20administration%20to%20stop%20defending%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flandmark-supreme-court-rulings-marriage-equality-in-us-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDefense%20of%20Marriage%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20since%20overturned%20law%20that%20banned%20federal%20recognition%20of%20same-sex%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Trump%20avoids%20enforcing%20the%20divest-or-ban%20law%2C%20it%20may%20not%20stand%20up%20to%20a%20legal%20challenge%2C%20as%20it's%20possible%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20will%20have%20already%20upheld%20its%20constitutionality%20by%20the%20time%20he%20attempts%20to%20ignore%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20Trump's%20Justice%20Department%20opts%20not%20to%20defend%20the%20law%2C%20Bloomberg's%20Schettenhelm%20said%20it%20could%20be%20risky%20for%20American%20companies%20like%20Apple%20and%20Google%20that%20host%20TikTok%20in%20app%20stores%20to%20keep%20it%20around.%20Trump%20has%20already%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-trump-changed-his-mind-on-tiktok-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eflip-flopped%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20TikTok%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-tiktok-ban-us-china-explained-in-30-seconds-2020-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eattempting%20to%20ban%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20then%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tiktok-deadline-september-15-2020-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eforce%20a%20sale%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20app%20in%202020.%20Who's%20to%20say%20that%20he%20may%20not%20change%20his%20mind%20again%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20sure%20they'd%20want%20to%20risk%20enormous%20liability%20on%20the%20hope%20that%20President%20Trump%20wouldn't%20change%20his%20mind%20and%20start%20enforcing%20the%20law%20against%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Schettenhelm%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c37a6b94-014a-4402-8322-8968e29dce20%5C%22%3EStrategy%20two%3A%20Act%20like%20the%20law%20doesn't%20apply%20to%20TikTok%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20could%20also%20claim%20that%20TikTok%20isn't%20subject%20to%20the%20divest-or-ban%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20one%20feels%20a%20bit%20absurd%2C%20as%20the%20bill%20specifically%20names%20TikTok%20and%20ByteDance%20as%20covered%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGavoor%20said%20it's%20possible%20that%20TikTok%20and%20ByteDance%20could%20reorganize%20so%20that%20they%20don't%20%26quot%3Btrigger%20the%20direct%20definition%20of%20their%20names%20or%20a%20subsidiary%20or%20a%20successor%20entity%26quot%3B%20under%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20variety%20of%20different%20potential%20corporate%20structures%20that%20they're%20undoubtedly%20considering%2C%26quot%3B%20Gavoor%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUniversity%20of%20Minnesota%20law%20professor%20Alan%20Rozenshtein%20also%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fastcompany.com%2F91223946%2Fwill-trump-ban-tiktok%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFast%20Company%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethat%20Trump%20could%20declare%20that%20ByteDance%20divested%20from%20TikTok%20without%20actually%20requiring%20it%20to%20do%20so.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20these%20approaches%20would%20attempt%20to%20skirt%20around%20the%20bill's%20language%20to%20avoid%20enforcing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECornell's%20Hans%20said%20any%20tactic%20a%20future%20Trump%20administration%20might%20take%20to%20keep%20TikTok%20aroun