%20bench%2C%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20DY%20Chandrachud%20-%20who%20authored%20the%20majority%20judgement%20on%20his%20last%20working%20day%20-%20struck%20down%20an%20earlier%20ruling%20that%20said%20an%20institution%20incorporated%20by%20a%20statute%20could%20not%20claim%20minority%20status%2C%20but%20left%20the%20question%20as%20it%20pertains%20to%20AMU%20to%20a%20regular%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20three%20dissenting%20judges%20on%20the%20Constitution%20bench%20today%20were%20Justices%20Surya%20Kant%2C%20Dipankar%20Datta%2C%20and%20SC%20Sharma%2C%20while%20three%20others%20-%20Justices%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%20(who%20will%20be%20the%20next%20Chief%20Justice)%2C%20JB%20Pardiwala%2C%20and%20Manoj%20Misra%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20outgoing%20Chief%20Justice%2C%20held%20the%20majority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20had%20earlier%20reserved%20its%20verdict%20on%20February%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EMajority%20Verdict%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReading%20for%20the%20majority%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20underlined%20the%20importance%20of%20identifying%20the%20university's%20actual%20point%20of%20origin%20-%20its%20genesis%20-%20to%20establish%20its%20minority%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBecause%20AMU%20had%20been%20'incorporated'%20by%20imperial%20legislation%20-%20it%20was%20founded%20in%201875%20as%20the%20Muhammadan%20Anglo-Oriental%20College%20and%20converted%20to%20a%20university%20by%20the%20British%20Raj%20in%201920%20-%20does%20not%20mean%20it%20was%20not%20'established'%20by%20members%20of%20a%20minority%20community%2C%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20key%20point%20is%20that%20the%20court%20said%20it%20is%20not%20necessary%20for%20an%20institution%20to%20be%20established%20only%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20a%20minority%20community%2C%20or%20for%20its%20administration%20to%20rest%20with%20members%20of%20that%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMinority%20institutions%20may%20also%20wish%20to%20emphasise%20secular%20education%2C%20it%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20test%2C%20the%20majority%20ruled%2C%20is%20to%20see%20if%20the%20administrative%20structure%20is%20in%20line%20with%20the%20claimed%20minority%20character%20of%20the%20institution%2C%20in%20this%20case%20the%20AMU.%20The%20court%20also%20said%20the%20government%20could%20regulate%20minority%20educational%20institutions%20as%20long%20as%20it%20does%20not%20infringe%20on%20the%20character%20of%20such%20institutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EDissent%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20dissenting%20judges%2C%20Justice%20Datta%20ruled%20the%20AMU%20is%20not%20a%20minority%20institution%2C%20while%20Justice%20Sharma%20noted%20a%20minority%20community%20should%20control%20institutions%20serving%20its%20peoples%20but%20with%20no%20interference.%20They%20must%2C%20however%2C%20also%20give%20its%20students%20the%20option%20of%20a%20secular%20education%2C%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ECase%20Background%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20Article%2030%20of%20the%20Constitution%20-%20which%20empowers%20religious%20and%20linguistic%20minorities%20to%20establish%20and%20administer%20educational%20institutions%20-%20AMU%20had%20enjoyed%20minority%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Aligarh%20Muslim%20University%20was%20founded%20in%201875%20and%20incorporated%20by%20imperial%20law%20in%201920.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%201951%20amendment%20to%20that%20imperial%20law%2C%20the%20AMU%20Act%2C%20did%20away%20with%20compulsory%20religious%20instructions%20for%20Muslim%20students.%20A%20second%20amendment%2C%20in%201981%2C%20sought%20to%20revert%20to%20the%20pre-1951%20position%20but%2C%20in%20the%20opinion%20of%20the%20Chief%20Justice-led%20majority%2C%20it%20did%20a%20%26quot%3Bhalf-hearted%20job%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20in%201967%2C%20a%20five-judge%20Constitution%20bench%20-%20in%20the%20S%20Azeez%20Basha%20versus%20Union%20of%20India%20case%20-%20held%20that%20since%20AMU%20is%20a%20central%20university%20it%20could%20not%20also%20be%20a%20minority%20institution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20arguments%2C%20which%20were%20held%20in%20February%2C%20Solicitor%20General%20Tushar%20Mehta%20and%20others%20said%20that%20because%20AMU%20had%2C%20since%20195%2C%20received%20significant%20funds%20-%20over%20Rs%205%2C000%20crore%20between%202019%20and%202023%20alone-%20from%20the%20central%20government%2C%20it%20had%20surrendered%20its%20minority%20character.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20in%202006%2C%20the%20Allahabad%20High%20Court%20dismissed%20the%201981%20amendment%2C%20holding%20that%20the%20AMU%20is%20not%20a%20minority%20institution.%20That%20matter%20was%20then%20referred%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20after%20the%20Congress-led%20UPA%20government%20at%20the%20centre%20appealed%20the%202006%20High%20Court%20verdict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20university%20had%20filed%20a%20separate%20petition%20against%20the%20same%20ruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20three-judge%20bench%20led%20by%20then%20Chief%20Justice%20Ranjan%20Gogoi%20sent%20this%20to%20the%20larger%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20the%20BJP-led%20union%20government%20-%20which%20said%20it%20would%20withdraw%20the%20appeal%20lodged%20by%20its%20Congress-led%20predecessor%20-%20refused%20to%20accept%20the%20contentious%201981%20amendment%20and%20sought%20to%20revert%20to%20the%20top%20court's%201967%20vedict%2C%20referring%20also%20to%20the%20issue%20of%20AMU%20using%20government%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731052380000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2Fqn1va0do_amu-ians_625x300_08_November_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Faligarh-muslim-university-a-minority-institution-new-supreme-court-bench-to-decide-6970678%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20seven-judge%20Constitution%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruled%204%3A3%20Friday%20to%20overturn%20a%20key%201967%20judgement%20on%20the%20Aligarh%2