al%20activity%20with%20compost%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20winter%2C%20microbial%20activity%20(the%20work%20carried%20out%20by%20tiny%20organisms%20in%20the%20soil)%20slows%20down%20due%20to%20the%20drop%20in%20temperature.%20This%20effect%20is%20particularly%20noticeable%20in%20colder%20states%20such%20as%20Punjab%2C%20Haryana%2C%20and%20Rajasthan%2C%20where%20temperatures%20can%20fall%20below%205%C2%B0C.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20winters%2C%20when%20we%20sow%2C%20it%20takes%20an%20extra%20couple%20of%20days%20for%20seeds%20to%20grow.%20In%20contrast%2C%20during%20monsoons%2C%20they%20sprout%20within%202-3%20days%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Savita.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20fewer%20organisms%20breaking%20down%20organic%20matter%2C%20the%20soil%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20recycle%20nutrients%20slows%20down%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20shortage%20of%20essential%20nutrients%20for%20crops.%20%E2%80%9CTo%20combat%20this%2C%20farmers%20can%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F341515%2Fiit-guwahati-organic-vermicompost-for-farmers-fast-biodegradation-technique-ajay-kalamdhad-mati-dhan%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadd%20compost%20or%20well-decomposed%20organic%20matter%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20winter%20sets%20in%20to%20support%20healthy%20microbial%20activity%20throughout%20the%20season%2C%E2%80%9D%20Savita%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E2.%20Prevent%20compaction%20with%20deep%20ploughing%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20wet%20soil%20freezes%2C%20it%20can%20harden%2C%20making%20it%20difficult%20for%20water%20to%20soak%20in%20and%20for%20plant%20roots%20to%20grow%20properly.%20This%20is%20a%20common%20problem%20in%20clayey%20soils%2C%20especially%20in%20regions%20like%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Bihar%2C%20and%20West%20Bengal.%20It%20particularly%20affects%20crops%20like%20rice%20and%20sugarcane%2C%20as%20they%20require%20loose%2C%20well-aerated%20soil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%